dfischer.proxysniffer

Class ProxySnifferVarSourceInlineScript

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.proxysniffer.ProxySnifferVarSourceDataInstance
      • dfischer.proxysniffer.ProxySnifferVarSourceInlineScript

  • public class ProxySnifferVarSourceInlineScript
extends ProxySnifferVarSourceDataInstance
    Var source for an "Inline Script" declaration.

    Note 1: An inline script may have no var extractors or var assigner - optional, do no delete if no var extractor (if not required).
    Note 2: If an inline script is bound to an url, you have to check in web admin (or in proxy sniffer) if the url call is still part of the load test.

    Since:
    V5.4-F

      • setExecPriority

        public void setExecPriority(int execPriority)
        Set the execution priority applied during the load test within the same execution scope. Scripts with the lowest execution priority are executed first, followed by scripts with a lower execution priority.
        Parameters:
        execPriority - the execution priority of the inline script. Non critical value, using the same execution priority for multiple scripts is allowed by may result in random execution order.

      • getExecPriority
